The paper deals with the problem of designing optimal linear precoding for a multi-user MIMO system, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The focus on large system analysis and asymptotic regime also suggests a potential connection to statistical learning theory and high-dimensional statistics, which are relevant to the machine learning community.
